---
alwaysApply: true
---

All integration tests must be written using Pest PHP.

Integration tests validate the Service layer with real database interaction — not through the HTTP layer.

Rules:

- Tests must live in `Modules/{Module}/Tests/Integration/`.
- Call service methods directly; do not use HTTP helpers (`postJson`, etc.).
- Use DTOs to call service methods as the service API requires.
- Use real database interaction; do not mock application services.
- Use factories to create test data.

- Tests must cover:
  - Successful execution
  - Domain/business rule failures (assert exceptions are thrown)
  - Edge cases

- Assert the returned model or scalar value.
- Assert database state when applicable.

- Use `RefreshDatabase` or `DatabaseTransactions` for isolation.
- Each test must be independent and deterministic.

- Avoid mocking unless testing external integrations (e.g. SMS, storage drivers).

- Tests must follow the AAA (Arrange / Act / Assert) pattern. Use clear Arrange/Act/Assert separation (comments are mandatory).
